wlsxPoEMIB.name: wlsxPoEMIB
wlsxPoEMIB.contactinfo: Postal: 1322 Crossman Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: dl-support@arubanetworks.com Phone: +1 408 227 4500
wlsxPoEMIB.description: This MIB module defines MIB objects which provide information about the Power Sourcing Equipment(PSE) and Powered Device(PD). The following abbreviations are defined in [IEEE-802.3af] and will be used with the same significance in this document: PSE - Power Sourcing Equipment; PD - Powered Device;

wlsxPsePortTable.name: wlsxPsePortTable
wlsxPsePortTable.description: A table of objects that display the parameters configured for a power ethernet port.

wlsxPsePortEntry.name: wlsxPsePortEntry
wlsxPsePortEntry.description: A set of objects that display the configuration of a power ethernet port.

wlsxPsePortIndex.name: wlsxPsePortIndex
wlsxPsePortIndex.description: This variable uniquely identifies the power ethernet port for which this entry is populated.

wlsxPsePortAdminStatus.name: wlsxPsePortAdminStatus
wlsxPsePortAdminStatus.description: Admin status of a power ethernet port. A value of enable(1) means that the port has PSE functions enabled on it. A value of disable(2) means that the port does not support or has disabled PSE functions.

wlsxPsePortState.name: wlsxPsePortState
wlsxPsePortState.description: This object indicates the status of the port. The reason for these states is indicated by wlsxPsePortStatus. on(1) - indicates that PSE is sourcing power. off(2) - indicates that PSE is not sourcing power.

wlsxPsePortStatus.name: wlsxPsePortStatus
wlsxPsePortStatus.description: This object indicates the status of the port. unknown(1) - indicates either a state of off with the reason being not known or the state is on. offAdmin(2) - indicates the port is administratively disabled. offPowerManagement(3) - indicates the port is off due to power management. offIllegalClass(4) - indicates the port is off because the PD is of illegal class. offDetectionProgress(5)- indicates the port is off because the PD detection is in progress. offHardwareError(6) - indicates the port is off because of hardware error. offNonStandardPd(7) - indicates the port is off because the PD is a non standard one.

wlsxPsePortDiscoveryMode.name: wlsxPsePortDiscoveryMode
wlsxPsePortDiscoveryMode.description: This object indicates the method of discovery used by the system for the detection of the Powered Device(PD). A value of unknown(0) means that the discovery method is unknown on this port. A value of off(1) means that the discovery method is turned off on this port. A value of ieee(2) indicates that the discovery method is IEEE based on this port. A value of cisco(3) indicates that the discovery method is Cisco based on this port.

wlsxPsePortIsPdDetected.name: wlsxPsePortIsPdDetected
wlsxPsePortIsPdDetected.description: This object indicates if a Powered Device(PD) is detected on this port.

wlsxPsePortIsIeeePd.name: wlsxPsePortIsIeeePd
wlsxPsePortIsIeeePd.description: This object indicates the IEEE compliance of a Powered Device(PD). A value of true(1) means the Powered Device(PD) is IEEE compliant. A value of false(2) means the Powered Device is not IEEE compliant.

wlsxPsePortPdClass.name: wlsxPsePortPdClass
wlsxPsePortPdClass.description: This object indicates the Power classification of the Powered Device(PD) connected on the port. A value of 'class0(1)' indicates that the power classification of the powered device falls into class 0 in IEEE specifications. A value of 'class1(2)' indicates that the power classification of the powered devices falls into class 1 in IEEE specifications. A value of 'class2(3)' indicates that the power classification of the powered devices falls into class 2 in IEEE specifications. A value of 'class3(4)' indicates that the power classification of the powered devices falls into class 3 in IEEE specifications. A value of 'class4(5)' indicates that the power classification of the powered devices falls into class 4 in IEEE specifications.

wlsxPsePortPriority.name: wlsxPsePortPriority
wlsxPsePortPriority.description: This object indicates the configured priority for this port. low(1) - indicates the priority of the port is low. high(2) - indicates the priority of the port is high. critical(3) - indicates the priority of the port is critical.

wlsxPsePortDefaultPowerMax.name: wlsxPsePortDefaultPowerMax
wlsxPsePortDefaultPowerMax.description: This object indicates the default maximum power available on this port.

wlsxPsePortPowerAllocated.name: wlsxPsePortPowerAllocated
wlsxPsePortPowerAllocated.description: This object indicates the configured power allocation on this port.

wlsxPsePortPowerConsumed.name: wlsxPsePortPowerConsumed
wlsxPsePortPowerConsumed.description: This object gives the power consumption by the PD on this port.

wlsxPsePortVoltage.name: wlsxPsePortVoltage
wlsxPsePortVoltage.description: This object indicates the voltage on this port.

wlsxPsePortCurrent.name: wlsxPsePortCurrent
wlsxPsePortCurrent.description: This object indicates the current on this port.

wlsxPseSlotTable.name: wlsxPseSlotTable
wlsxPseSlotTable.description: A table of objects that display all the details about the Power Sourcing Equipment(PSE).

wlsxPseSlotEntry.name: wlsxPseSlotEntry
wlsxPseSlotEntry.description: A set of objects that displays all the information about the PSE on this device on a per slot basis.

wlsxPseSlotIndex.name: wlsxPseSlotIndex
wlsxPseSlotIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies a PSE entry.

wlsxPseSlotPowerAvailable.name: wlsxPseSlotPowerAvailable
wlsxPseSlotPowerAvailable.description: This object indicates the total amount of power available from this PSE.

wlsxPseSlotPowerConsumption.name: wlsxPseSlotPowerConsumption
wlsxPseSlotPowerConsumption.description: This object indicates the total amount of power consumed from this PSE.

wlsxPseSlotGuardBand.name: wlsxPseSlotGuardBand
wlsxPseSlotGuardBand.description: This object indicates the power left unused to be provided in case of spikes in the amount of power used.

wlsxPseSlotPoEManagementMode.name: wlsxPseSlotPoEManagementMode
wlsxPseSlotPoEManagementMode.description: This object indicates the PSE management mode. A value of dynamic(1) indicates that it is dynamic power management. A value of static(2) indicates that it is static power management. A value of class(3) indicates that it is a Class based power management.

wlsxTrapInterfacePoEState.name: wlsxTrapInterfacePoEState
wlsxTrapInterfacePoEState.description: When there is a PoE state transition i.e on or off then this trap is sent to the management entity

wlsxPoEMIBCompliance.name: wlsxPoEMIBCompliance
wlsxPoEMIBCompliance.description: This is the statement of compliance.

wlsxPoEMIBPortGroup.name: wlsxPoEMIBPortGroup
wlsxPoEMIBPortGroup.description: This group provides the details of all the Power ethernet ports on the device.

wlsxPoEMIBMainPseGroup.name: wlsxPoEMIBMainPseGroup
wlsxPoEMIBMainPseGroup.description: This group provides the details of the PSE entry.

wlsxPoEMIBNotificationsGroup.name: wlsxPoEMIBNotificationsGroup
wlsxPoEMIBNotificationsGroup.description: This group gives the collection of Notifications related to power consumption on an port.
